    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1982-08-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1982-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="17"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d17">
                <head>17. Memorandum From Richard Pipes of the <rs corresp="recqAPrajNMdo0x5k"
                        type="topic">National Security</rs> Council Staff to the President’s
                    Assistant for <rs corresp="recqAPrajNMdo0x5k" type="topic">National
                        Security</rs> Affairs (Clark)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d17fn1"
                        >Source: Reagan Library, Executive Secretariat, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                            >NSC</gloss> National Security Decision Directives (<gloss
                            target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>) Files, <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1"
                            >NSDD</gloss> 54 9/2/1982. Secret. Sent for action. Copies were sent to
                        Dobriansky and <persName corresp="#p_SW_1">Stearman</persName>. “Signed” is
                        stamped at the top of the memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1982-08-26">August 26, 1982</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <!--<pb facs="d17-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d17-2"/>-->
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> on Eastern Europe</item>
                </list>
                <p>As State and Commerce were unable to agree upon mutually satisfactory language to
                    define our policy on <rs corresp="recIW1xgHEanEAKPW" type="topic">Technology
                        Transfer</rs> in the <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss> on Eastern
                    Europe, I recommend that the original text at Tab A be used.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d17fn2">Not found attached. See <ref target="#d12">Document
                        12</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>State, Defense and <persName corresp="#p_BN_1">Norman Bailey</persName> concur
                    with this decision.<note n="3" xml:id="d17fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BN_1">Bailey</persName> initialed his concurrence
                        above his name.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="sectiontitleital">Recommendation</p>
                <p>That you forward the memorandum at Tab I to the President with the text of the
                        <gloss target="#t_NSDD_1">NSDD</gloss>.<note n="4" xml:id="d17fn4">The
                        “Approve” option was checked. Underneath the recommendations and written in
                        an unknown hand, is the notation “9/1/82 WPC s/memo to Pres. Copy will be
                        Dacom’ed to Pres.” The memorandum to Reagan, who was at his ranch in
                        California August 26–31, was not found attached.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
